news_header: Yesterday, due to a self-error, Nordnet's online customers briefly accessed other customers' accounts. One confirmed case involved a Finnish customer who made transactions that were later cancelled without financial damage. Nordnet is investigating the issue caused by a defective software component and has contacted affected customers.
news_original_title: Nordnet: Ainakin yhden suomalaisasiakkaan tilillä tehty luvattomia transaktioita – Kaupat peruttu
news_text: The company will notify the Swedish data protection authority within 72 hours. Officials emphasized the seriousness of the incident, noting that no unauthorized withdrawals were possible.
